   influence of sedimentary pore water indicating that these carbonates
   were formed under reducing conditions below or at the seafloor. Their
   Th-230/U-234 ages span a time interval from 0.8 to 6.4 ka and cluster
   around 1.2 and 4.7 ka. In contrast, chemoherm carbonates precipitate
