   phase relationship enables us to reduce the magnitudes of age
   uncertainties for aggradational sections corresponding to glacial
   terminations IX through III, which we had dated previously by
   Ar-40/Ar-39 methods. Glacial terminations VIII, VI, and IV precede
   beyond 95\% confidence the ages predicted by Northern Hemisphere summer
